div.note:
Ground elm bark (  nire
              ) when combined with salt functioned as a preservative that inhibited the growth of certain bacteria.
             Glutamic acid may also lend the salt-pickles a more complex flavor.

div.p:
16
                mats  〈4 are to be hung up in the Grains Bureau, 4 are for drying
             various produce, 4 are for covering royal tables, 4 are for grinding salt and elm〉; 16 wild rice mats 〈8 are to
             be hung up in the Grains Bureau, 8 are to be used as a concealing curtain at the Royal Meal Station〉;
             sinomenium, 6  kin  〈to be hung up in the Grains Bureau and to attach to the
             mats [listed above]〉;

24
             roasting dishes 〈for roasting various dehydrated grains〉; 11 large lids 〈for the jugs〉; 24 strainer baskets
             〈for scooping boiled mochi〉;

As
             for the royal provisions from E in Yamashiro Province, the governor (  kokushi 
             ) is to order the custodian (  azukaribito  ) to send fish.
